The idea is fairly simple. Just keeping a track of the shortest match where the string from start and end are equal. In case, such a string is found, apply the same logic on remaining string. In case, no match is found, return 0 if string is empty, else 1.

```
def longestDecomposition(self, text: str) -> int:
        n = len(text)
        start = ''
        end = ''
        for i in range(n // 2):
            start += text[i]
            end = text[n - i - 1] + end
            if start == end:
                return 2 + self.longestDecomposition(text[i + 1: n - i - 1])
        return 0 if n == 0 else 1
```

