# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
This is best problem which can be solved using `z-function`. 

`Definition of z-function :` 
Suppose we are given a string  $s$  of length  $n$ . The Z-function for this string is an array of length  $n$  where the  $i$ -th element is equal to the greatest number of characters starting from the position  $i$  that coincide with the first characters of  $s$ . 

Here we call Z_function and get the last best prefix. Untill last best prefix is zero.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
$$O(N^2)$$

- Space complexity:
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
$$O(N)$$

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    int z_function(string s) {
        int n = s.size();

        vector<int> z(n);
        for(int i = 1, l =0, r = 0; i<n; ++i) {
            if(i<=r)
                z[i] = min(r - i +1, z[i-l]);
            while(i+z[i] < n && s[z[i]] == s[i + z[i] ]) ++z[i];

            if(i+ z[i] -1 > r) {
                l = i; r = i+z[i]-1;
            } 

        }

        for(int i = n-1; i>=0; --i) {
            if(z[i] + i == n) return z[i];
        }
        return 0;
    }

    int longestDecomposition(string text) {
        int n = text.size();
        int start = 0, end = n-1, ans = 0;
        while(start <= end) {
            int len = z_function(text.substr(start, end-start+1));

            start +=len;
            end -= len;
            if(len == 0) {
                ++ans;
                break;
            } else {
                ans+=2;
            }

        }
        return ans;
    }
};
```

