## **Explanation**
Sort by 2 keys.
@v_paliy note that:
"count[x] sorts by frequency, and if two values are equal, it will sort the keys in decreasing order."
<br>

## **Complexity**
Time `O(NlogN)`
Space `O(N)`
<br>

**C++**
```cpp
    vector<int> frequencySort(vector<int>& A) {
        unordered_map<int, int> count;
        for (int a: A)
            count[a]++;
        sort(begin(A), end(A), [&](int a, int b) {
            return count[a] == count[b] ? a > b : count[a] < count[b];
        });
        return A;
    }
```
