Return the count of strings `s` of the input array `A` which are substrings of the target `t`.

Note: we can use [Rabin-Karp](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rabin%E2%80%93Karp_algorithm) or [Boyer-Moore](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Boyer%E2%80%93Moore_string-search_algorithm) as optimizations for finding a substring within a string.

