solutions.content:
The problem statement said that we have to match each ```pattern``` element character with ```word``` substring. 

### Algorithm:
- First we assign a variable ```count``` to ```0```.
- We iterate all the element of the array.
- Check whether each element character match  with ```word``` substring or not 
- If the above condition fulfiled then we increment ```count``` variable ```1```
- After finish the execution of iteration, we will return ```count``` 

#### Solve with JavaScript ```includes``` method
```
var numOfStrings = function(patterns, word) {
    let count =0;
    for(value of patterns){
        if(word.includes(value)){
            count++;
        }
    }
    return count;
};
```

#### Solve with JavaScript ```indexOf``` method

```
var numOfStrings = function(patterns, word) {
    let count = 0;
    for(let i=0;i<patterns.length;i++){
        if(word.indexOf(patterns[i])!== -1){
            count++;
        }
    }
    return count;
};
```
#### Solve with JavaScript ```reduce``` method

```
var numOfStrings = function(patterns, word) {
    let result = patterns.reduce((acc,curr)=>{
        if(word.includes(curr)){
            acc++
        }
        return acc
    },0);

    return result;
};
```

